data.title: The Global Professional Tennis Coach Association (GPTCA)
data.meta_description: (GPTCA) is an international organization dedicated to educating, training, and assisting professional tennis coaches who wish to evolve at the ATP World Tour.
data.text:
GPTCA A* Level International Coach

Currently involved with Marinko Matosevic (ATP Career High #39) for most of 2014

2009-2013

Coach of AUS Jr Davis Cup team

2003-2004

Coach of AUS Fed Cup team

Winner of 17 Grand Slam titles

Career high of #19 in singles on ATP Tour

Career high of #1 in doubles on ATP Tour

Singles Career Titles: 4

Doubles Career Titles: 67

2000 Sydney

Olympic Silver Medallist (w/Woodbridge)

1999

Davis Cup winner

1996 Atlanta

Olympic Gold Medallist (w/Woodbridge)

Member of International Tennis Hall Of Fame

Member of Sport Australia Hall Of Fame

Member of Australian Tennis Hall Of Fame

Member of Sth Aust Sports Hall Of Fame
